.cursorrules
# PROJECT: Kalorimetre (AI-Powered Professional Dietitian Companion)
# ROLE: Senior Full-Stack Engineer, AI Integration Expert, UX Architect

## CORE ARCHITECTURE & UX PARADIGM
- Tech: React.js, Vite, Tailwind CSS, LocalStorage, Framer Motion (for animations).
- Language: 100% TURKISH for all UI texts.
- Themes: "Açık" (Light - #F8FAFC), "Koyu" (Dark - #0C0F1A), and "AMOLED Siyah" (#000000).
- Design System: Premium minimal, rounded-2xl cards, emerald green (#10B981) primary. NO white gaps between calendar grid cells. Perfect flex-center alignment for all icons.

## NEW CORE LOGIC: DIETITIAN VS MANUAL MODE
- Two main operation modes defined in Onboarding:
  1. Manual Mode (Mifflin-St Jeor calculated macros).
  2. Dietitian Mode (AI OCR extracted meal plans from a photo/PDF).
- Health Profile: Users must explicitly select health conditions (Diabetes, Hypertension, Allergies) which strictly filters all AI meal suggestions.

## FEATURE SCOPE & REQUIREMENTS
1. ONBOARDING & HEALTH PROFILE
   - Auth screen (Google/Email).
   - "Diyetisyen Listemi Yükle (OCR)" vs "Kendi Hedefimi Belirle" split.
   - Comprehensive Health Profile selection step.
2. DASHBOARD (Ana Panel & Timeline)
   - TOP: "Günlük Özet & AI Asistan". Proactive limits warning (e.g., "Öğlende fazla protein alındı, akşam dengelenecek").
   - MIDDLE: "Planlanan (Liste)" vs "Gerçekleşen (Tüketilen)" comparative timeline UI.
   - ACTION: "Birebir Aynısını Yedim" (Ate Exactly This) quick-log button.
3. LOG FOOD & DYNAMIC ALTERNATIVES
   - When a user taps a planned meal, offer a "Bunun yerine ne yiyebilirim?" button.
   - AI generates alternatives strictly based on the Health Profile (e.g., low GI for diabetics).
4. HISTORY & ADVANCED ANALYTICS
   - Monthly Heatmap Grid (Flawless CSS, no white gaps, perfectly centered icons).
   - End-of-week adherence evaluation reports.
   - Scale Receipt OCR: Placeholder UI to upload body comp scale receipts (Fat, Muscle) and visualize.
5. PROFILE & SETTINGS
   - Edit Health Profile, Theme, Target, and Water Goal.
   - CRITICAL: When editing personal data, show the recalculated TDEE LIVE on the screen before saving.

## CODING RULES
- Build pure, modular Tailwind CSS components. Do not use absolute positioning from designs.
- For OCR and AI Generation features (Diet list scanning, dynamic alternatives), build the full UI but use mock `setTimeout` functions returning simulated JSON data until backend API keys are connected.